      "createdAt": "2025-05-27T09:06:50.000Z",
      "author": "JHarrington (Jen H)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Thank you Iryna<br />\nI know they are there, but you cannot see that a file has been attached to a task without clicking into the Files Gallery. I am guessing there isn’t a way to extract the file from the updates and add it to a Files column. This makes sense since there could be multiple Files Columns on a board.<br />\nWould be great if an automation could be developed to accommodate this <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/blush.png?v=14\" title=\":blush:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":blush:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /></p>\n<table>\n</table><table>\n</table><table>\n</table><table>\n</table><table>\n</table><table>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>\n<p><a href=\"https://us.content.exclaimer.net/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.npn360.com%2F&amp;tenantid=AC2Ng6QiEeqbBQANOhMLNA&amp;templateid=39f3be703130f011a5f100224826a7ba&amp;excomponentid=_fCdoAIvrFEjhHktLQxKsdULbw66eUJghtzACtUqipk&amp;excomponenttype=Image&amp;signature=ZUj1qWfHi53q-KvGvWts9Q5McMzeRUItbPuNTahSHYLFX_M3ekVPzMtwUkuCu7dYX3xF8EjLgDp5SNmkl5N7eaKYEp3iZw5LISAOPDehxg7NubJQrhdT5yKLyCQZqsQMvyg2G_sdVqmGnN6A4VxOCEBqlCPH89E70MXkeLC5iP-Pn0lMLpEgD4i20dmUrGZ7sAY1bKiibEctWzgr8Rqc475mO1P7cCcVXOQZSERx1Rmg_FTFZN_e4WHHeeLIQDFGz0W0aqoW77wGXzSK6CXKwKZxUp-vaqPfJH-Qlf4aFg06ImO_RvnPKxFqMZ_Usm4McwUlUaypWh4jv7xS0UTd5Q&amp;v=1&amp;imprintMessageId=b679b447-5cca-427f-8031-2110b25b9ed2\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/5/9/5968c4813e9f7db875f97ddd3029990be8056ff2.png\" width=\"74\" height=\"65\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table><table>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>\n<p><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/5/d/5d62e0a030b27ad35ad2d77d2acc422170154cc0.png\" width=\"13\" height=\"86\" alt=\"\" /></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table><table>\n</table><table>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>\n<p>Jennifer Harrington</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Operational Excellence Manager</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table><table>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>\n