      "author": "JCorrell (Jim - The Monday Man)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p><a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/jharrington\">@JHarrington</a> <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/yuvrajsingh\">@YuvrajSingh</a></p>\n<p>The marketplace app <a href=\"https://monday.com/marketplace/listing/10000123/update-magic-1\">Update Magic</a> has a recipe that does that:<br />\n</p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/1/f/1f853fa6430362929d409f33f54229c3e9b9aa24.png\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/1/f/1f853fa6430362929d409f33f54229c3e9b9aa24.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"375\" height=\"303\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">501×404 18.1 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Jim - <a href=\"https://TheMondayMan.com\">The Monday Man</a><br />\n<strong><a href=\"https://themondayman.com/custom/\">Get Custom Apps, Integrations &amp; Automations for monday</a></strong></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": 230735,
      "postNumber": 9,
      "createdAt": "2025-05-28T12:27:36.114Z",
      "author": "KamalDeepPareek (Kamal Deep Pareek)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Yes, you can automate file updates from the Updates Bubble to a Files column without AI by using built-in automation tools or integrations like Zapier or Integromat (Make). Set a trigger for when a file is added or updated in the Updates Bubble, then create an action to copy or move that file link or attachment into the Files column. This approach avoids extra AI-related costs and stays within your action limits. Check if your platform supports native automation rules or simple workflows to handle this transfer efficiently without exceeding your budget or action limits.</p>"
    },
